By R standards, you'll only be able to list one maintainer in the package DESCRIPTION; but if they are not already added as a contributor that would be good to add.  We can grant extra push access to the package but that needs to be done on our side. We will need to create a BiocCredentials account for the new additional 'maintainer' (if they do not already have one) which requires an email and (optionally) github username.   Once provided we can create the account and grant access;  I will email the other colleague with how to active their account.

Cheers,


