Message-ID: <CACGEUzZ1Ow2vpf1D2VFjJY6YebwPSAOxSN880NwhF1mfvd4gew@mail.gmail.com>

Hi Everyone,
Bioconductor is currently seeking new members to join its code of conduct
(CoC) committee. If you wish to contribute to the community and experience
being part of a committee to connect with international people operating
within Bioconductor, consider putting your name down:
https://forms.gle/DPxyubQotSsd3iD1A.

*What is the Bioconductor CoC committee?*
Code of Conducts (CoCs) play a crucial role in maintaining the integrity
and safety of online communities and open source projects by setting
standards for behaviour and the Bioconductor CoC committee is responsible
for enforcing and upholding them in this community.
*What level of commitment is expected if I apply?*
The CoC only meets 3 to 4 times per year, and always for a good reason.
This allows members to also participate across other boards of the
consortium.

*Need more information?*
If you want more information feel free to contact myself or my current
co-chair of the committee Gerry Tonkin-Hill, cc'ed here.
You can also find all current committee members and read the CoC here:
https://www.bioconductor.org/about/code-of-conduct/.

Best,

Anna

-- 
